sec.p:
The ability to represent data in a generic way, as explained above, greatly simplifies data processing. The latter can be described as the following three simple steps:
Read data from a web address, representing an ot:Compound or an ot:Dataset instance;
Perform processing; store results as ot:Dataset representation (e.g. ot:FeatureValue instances);
Write the ot:Dataset RDF representation to an OpenTox data service; return the URI of the resulting dataset.
